  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: go-ethereum library\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\n`types.NewEIP155Signer(chainID).Sender(signedTx)` should return the same address as `crypto.PubkeyToAddress(privateKey.PublicKey)` returns.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\n`types.NewEIP155Signer(chainID).Sender(signedTx)` returns random (but always the same) address.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nRun:\r\n\r\n```go\r\nprivateKey, _ := crypto.GenerateKey()\r\n\r\nnonce, _ := transactions.Client.PendingNonceAt(context.Background(), crypto.PubkeyToAddress(privateKey.PublicKey))\r\ngasPrice, _ := transactions.Client.SuggestGasPrice(context.Background())\r\ngasLimit := uint64(21000)\r\namount := big.NewInt(10000000)\r\nvar data []byte\r\ntx := types.NewTransaction(nonce, common.HexToAddress(\"0xfee66065C536A28000CfECF272A351592DA8473d\"), amount, gasLimit, gasPrice, data)\r\nsignedTx, _ := types.SignTx(tx, types.NewEIP155Signer(big.NewInt(1), privateKey)\r\n\r\nfmt.Println(crypto.PubkeyToAddress(privateKey.PublicKey))\r\nfmt.Println(types.NewEIP155Signer(big.NewInt(1)).Sender(signedTx))\r\n```\r\nYou'll see that address on first output line (with which the tx was signed) is different from address on the second line.",
